Miss Merle is the owner of a local plantation. Miss Merle is generally a kindly lady whom Janey describes as being fat with a nice round face. Miss Merle feels deeply concerned about Candy, whom she played a role in raising. She also mobilizes Candy's effort to save Mathu. Miss Merle is a member of the ruling white class who distinguishes herself clearly from the blacks around her. Still, Miss Merle differs greatly from Jack and Bea Marshall by being both aware and active in the community. Overall, Miss Merle is a nice generous female character who seems slightly sad. She carries unrequited love for Jack Marshall and her attachment to Candy suggests that she may not have had children of her own.